    "Obrix"
  ],
  "description": "A localized surge — not a full storm but an intense electrical event in a defined zone. Noise src1 through BP at 2600 Hz (higher than Flash Storm, more 'electrical crackle' vs 'ionized roar'). proc1Reso=0.82 — very high resonance produces a distinct tonal center within the noise. gestureMode=3 (Tide/Surge), flashTrigger=0.68. proc2=LP (4200 Hz) cuts only the extreme highs, keeping the surge bright and piercing. proc3=RingMod (proc3Type=5, 880 Hz) on the merged signal adds metallic electrical artifacts. aggression=0.65. LFO->FilterCutoff (0.88 Hz, fast sweep for electrical flutter), Env->FilterReso (surge tightens on attack), Velocity->Volume (discharge intensity), Aftertouch->Pan (surge direction). MOVEMENT macro 0.38.",
